						<div class="postbody">Great!<br />I did as you said and tested on an emulator.<br />Worked like a charm! Thank you for the tip!! <img src="./images/smilies/Mfr_icon_homebrew.png" alt=":beer:" title="Beer" /> <br /><br />I'm thinking in put sockets on all of this clone's ICs, would this be a good idea?<br />I'll try to reassemble at least the enough for it to boot tomorrow. <br />I'll try post new stuff as they're happening. <br />Just in case someone else is viewing this and is &quot;cheering&quot; for me. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_mrgreen.gif" alt=":mrgreen:" title="Mr. Green" />  <br /><br />I don't know if it's visible in the pictures, but there's a lot of opaque stuff that gives this board a kind of &quot;dirty&quot; visual.<br />I removed a decent amount of it, but to fully remove it i think the only way is to take all the parts out, clean and them reassemble.<br />Would this be worth the effort?<br />I mean, it lasted more than 20 years, and a good amount of this time it was on a (very) less than ideal storage.<br />I know this sounds kind of a &quot;generical retoric sentimental&quot; question, but would this fix make this clone resist for about more 30 years (or even more) or it's really not necessary (would this be just a cosmetic fix)?<br /><br />I really would love to show the stuff I'm fixing / building / transforming now to my grandsons in the future... <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /><br />The experience of showing my kids the games and toys I used to play when I was at their age is being great!!<br />And they're enjoying each new cartridge I build, fix or mod. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif" alt=":D" title="Very Happy" /></div>

